Variables clave: Overall, Interest in science, support for scientific inquiry, #####income index, health index, education index, HDI

Modelo GAM

# k representa el numero de funciones de paso
GamModel <- gam(Overall ~ s(Interest, k=3) +
                  s(Support, k = 3) + 
                  s(Income, k= 3) + 
                  s(Health, k=3) +
                  s(Edu, k = 3) + 
                  s(HDI, k = 3),
                            data = datos)
# RepresentaciÃ³n grÃ¡fica
plot(GamModel, residuals = TRUE, pch = 1)

coef(GamModel)
##   (Intercept) s(Interest).1 s(Interest).2  s(Support).1  s(Support).2 
##  4.711538e+02 -2.530803e-11 -2.739965e+01 -1.774794e+01  8.468927e+00

GAM ampliando K

GamModel2 <- gam(Overall ~ s(Interest, k=5) +
                                s(Support, k = 5) + 
                                s(Income, k= 5) + 
                                s(Health, k=5) +
                                s(Edu, k = 5) + 
                                s(HDI, k = 5),
                              data = datos)
plot(GamModel2, residuals = TRUE, pch = 1)

Cambiando el parametro âsmoothingâ

GamModel3 <- gam(Overall ~ s(Interest, k=3) +
                   s(Support, k = 3) + 
                   s(Income, k= 3) + 
                   s(Health, k=3) +
                   s(Edu, k = 3) + 
                   s(HDI, k = 3),
                 data = datos, sp = 0.01)
## Warning in gam.setup(formula = structure(list(pf = Overall ~ 1, pfok = 1, :
## Supplied smoothing parameter vector is too short - ignored.
plot(GamModel3, residuals = TRUE, pch = 1)

coef(GamModel3)
##   (Intercept) s(Interest).1 s(Interest).2  s(Support).1  s(Support).2 
##  4.711538e+02 -2.530803e-11 -2.739965e+01 -1.774794e+01  8.468927e+00
